decl: example : s ∩ t ∪ s ∩ u ⊆ s ∩ (t ∪ u)
og_raw:
example : s ∩ t ∪ s ∩ u ⊆ s ∩ (t ∪ u)  := by
  rintro x (⟨xs, xt⟩ | ⟨xs, xu⟩)
  · use xs; left; exact xt
  . use xs; right; exact xu
new_raw:
example : s ∩ t ∪ s ∩ u ⊆ s ∩ (t ∪ u)   := by
  rintro x (⟨xs, xt⟩ | ⟨xs, xu⟩)
  exact ⟨xs, Or.inl xt⟩
  exact ⟨xs, Or.inr xu⟩

decl: example : s \ (t ∪ u) ⊆ (s \ t) \ u
og_raw:
example : s \ (t ∪ u) ⊆ (s \ t) \ u  := by
  rintro x ⟨xs, xntu⟩
  constructor
  use xs
  · intro xt
    exact xntu (Or.inl xt)
  intro xu
  apply xntu (Or.inr xu)
new_raw:
example : s \ (t ∪ u) ⊆ (s \ t) \ u   := by
  rintro x ⟨xs, xntu⟩
  exact ⟨⟨xs, fun xt => xntu (Or.inl xt)⟩, fun xu => xntu (Or.inr xu)⟩

decl: example : s ∩ (s ∪ t) = s
og_raw:
example : s ∩ (s ∪ t) = s  := by
  ext x; constructor
  · rintro ⟨xs, _⟩
    exact xs
  . intro xs
    use xs; left; exact xs
new_raw:
example : s ∩ (s ∪ t) = s   := by
  exact Set.ext fun x => ⟨fun ⟨xs, _⟩ => xs, fun xs => ⟨xs, Or.inl xs⟩⟩

og_raw:

  ext x; constructor
  · rintro (xs | ⟨xs, xt⟩) <;> exact xs
  . intro xs; left; exact xs
new_raw:
example : s ∪ s ∩ t = s   := by
  exact Set.ext fun x => ⟨fun | Or.inl xs | Or.inr ⟨xs, _⟩ => xs, fun xs => Or.inl xs⟩

decl: example : s \ t ∪ t = s ∪ t
og_raw:
example : s \ t ∪ t = s ∪ t  := by
  ext x; constructor
  · rintro (⟨xs, nxt⟩ | xt)
    · left
      exact xs
    . right
      exact xt
  by_cases h : x ∈ t
  · intro
    right
    exact h
  rintro (xs | xt)
  · left
    use xs
  right; exact xt
new_raw:
example : s \ t ∪ t = s ∪ t  := by
  ext x; constructor
  · rintro (⟨xs, nxt⟩ | xt)
    · left
      exact xs
    . right
      exact xt
  by_cases h : x ∈ t
  · intro
    right
    exact h
  rintro (xs | xt)
  · left
    use xs
  right; exact xt

decl: example : s \ t ∪ t \ s = (s ∪ t) \ (s ∩ t)
og_raw:
example : s \ t ∪ t \ s = (s ∪ t) \ (s ∩ t)  := by
  ext x; constructor
  · rintro (⟨xs, xnt⟩ | ⟨xt, xns⟩)
    · constructor
      left
      exact xs
      rintro ⟨_, xt⟩
      contradiction
    . constructor
      right
      exact xt
      rintro ⟨xs, _⟩
      contradiction
  rintro ⟨xs | xt, nxst⟩
  · left
    use xs
    intro xt
    apply nxst
    constructor <;> assumption
  . right; use xt; intro xs
    apply nxst
    constructor <;> assumption
new_raw:
example : s \ t ∪ t \ s = (s ∪ t) \ (s ∩ t)   := by
  ext x; constructor
  rintro (⟨xs, xnt⟩ | ⟨xt, xns⟩)
  · exact ⟨Or.inl xs, fun ⟨_, h⟩ => xnt h⟩
  · exact ⟨Or.inr xt, fun ⟨h, _⟩ => xns h⟩
  rintro ⟨xs | xt, h⟩
  · left; exact ⟨xs, fun xt => h ⟨xs, xt⟩⟩
  · right; exact ⟨xt, fun xs => h ⟨xs, xt⟩⟩

decl: example : { n | Nat.Prime n } ∩ { n | n > 2 } ⊆ { n | ¬Even n }
og_raw:
example : { n | Nat.Prime n } ∩ { n | n > 2 } ⊆ { n | ¬Even n }  := by
  intro n
  simp
  intro nprime
  rcases Nat.Prime.eq_two_or_odd nprime with h | h
  · rw [h]
    intro
    linarith
  rw [Nat.even_iff, h]
  norm_num
new_raw:
example : { n | Nat.Prime n } ∩ { n | n > 2 } ⊆ { n | ¬Even n }   := by
  intro n
  simp
  intro nprime _
  rcases Nat.Prime.eq_two_or_odd nprime with h | h
  rw [h]; linarith
  rw [Nat.even_iff, h]; norm_num

  · apply h₀ x (ssubt xs)

  intro x xs

decl: example : (s ∪ ⋂ i, A i) = ⋂ i, A i ∪ s
og_raw:
example : (s ∪ ⋂ i, A i) = ⋂ i, A i ∪ s  := by
  ext x
  simp only [mem_union, mem_iInter]
  constructor
  · rintro (xs | xI)
    · intro i
      right
      exact xs
    intro i
    left
    exact xI i
  intro h
  by_cases xs : x ∈ s
  · left
    exact xs
  right
  intro i
  cases h i
  · assumption
  contradiction
new_raw:
example : (s ∪ ⋂ i, A i) = ⋂ i, A i ∪ s   := by
  ext x
  simp only [mem_union, mem_iInter]
  constructor
  · exact fun | Or.inl xs => fun _ => Or.inr xs | Or.inr xI => fun i => Or.inl (xI i)
  · exact fun h => (em (x ∈ s)).elim Or.inl (fun xs => Or.inr (fun i => (h i).resolve_right xs))

og_raw:

  rw [pow_two, Nat.prime_two.dvd_mul] at h
  cases h <;> assumption
new_raw:

decl: example {m n : ℕ} (coprime_mn : m.Coprime n) : m ^ 2 ≠ 2 * n ^ 2
og_raw:
example {m n : ℕ} (coprime_mn : m.Coprime n) : m ^ 2 ≠ 2 * n ^ 2  := by
  intro sqr_eq
  have : 2 ∣ m := by
    apply even_of_even_sqr
    rw [sqr_eq]
    apply dvd_mul_right
  obtain ⟨k, meq⟩ := dvd_iff_exists_eq_mul_left.mp this
  have : 2 * (2 * k ^ 2) = 2 * n ^ 2 := by
    rw [← sqr_eq, meq]
    ring
  have : 2 * k ^ 2 = n ^ 2 :=
    (mul_right_inj' (by norm_num)).mp this
  have : 2 ∣ n := by
    apply even_of_even_sqr
    rw [← this]
    apply dvd_mul_right
  have : 2 ∣ m.gcd n := by
    apply Nat.dvd_gcd <;>
    assumption
  have : 2 ∣ 1 := by
    convert this
    symm
    exact coprime_mn
  norm_num at this
new_raw:
example {m n : ℕ} (coprime_mn : m.Coprime n) : m ^ 2 ≠ 2 * n ^ 2  := by
  intro sqr_eq
  have : 2 ∣ m := by
    apply even_of_even_sqr
    rw [sqr_eq]
    apply dvd_mul_right
  obtain ⟨k, meq⟩ := dvd_iff_exists_eq_mul_left.mp this
  have : 2 * (2 * k ^ 2) = 2 * n ^ 2 := by
    rw [← sqr_eq, meq]
    ring
  have : 2 * k ^ 2 = n ^ 2 :=
    (mul_right_inj' (by norm_num)).mp this
  have : 2 ∣ n := by
    apply even_of_even_sqr
    rw [← this]
    apply dvd_mul_right
  have : 2 ∣ m.gcd n := by
    apply Nat.dvd_gcd <;>
    assumption
  have : 2 ∣ 1 := by
    convert this
    symm
    exact coprime_mn
  norm_num at this

decl: example {m n p : ℕ} (coprime_mn : m.Coprime n) (prime_p : p.Prime) : m ^ 2 ≠ p * n ^ 2
og_raw:
example {m n p : ℕ} (coprime_mn : m.Coprime n) (prime_p : p.Prime) : m ^ 2 ≠ p * n ^ 2  := by
  intro sqr_eq
  have : p ∣ m := by
    apply prime_p.dvd_of_dvd_pow
    rw [sqr_eq]
    apply dvd_mul_right
  obtain ⟨k, meq⟩ := dvd_iff_exists_eq_mul_left.mp this
  have : p * (p * k ^ 2) = p * n ^ 2 := by
    rw [← sqr_eq, meq]
    ring
  have : p * k ^ 2 = n ^ 2 := by
    apply (mul_right_inj' _).mp this
    exact prime_p.ne_zero
  have : p ∣ n := by
    apply prime_p.dvd_of_dvd_pow
    rw [← this]
    apply dvd_mul_right
  have : p ∣ Nat.gcd m n := by apply Nat.dvd_gcd <;> assumption
  have : p ∣ 1 := by
    convert this
    symm
    exact coprime_mn
  have : 2 ≤ 1 := by
    apply prime_p.two_le.trans
    exact Nat.le_of_dvd zero_lt_one this
  norm_num at this
new_raw:
example {m n p : ℕ} (coprime_mn : m.Coprime n) (prime_p : p.Prime) : m ^ 2 ≠ p * n ^ 2  := by
  intro sqr_eq
  have : p ∣ m := by
    apply prime_p.dvd_of_dvd_pow
    rw [sqr_eq]
    apply dvd_mul_right
  obtain ⟨k, meq⟩ := dvd_iff_exists_eq_mul_left.mp this
  have : p * (p * k ^ 2) = p * n ^ 2 := by
    rw [← sqr_eq, meq]
    ring
  have : p * k ^ 2 = n ^ 2 := by
    apply (mul_right_inj' _).mp this
    exact prime_p.ne_zero
  have : p ∣ n := by
    apply prime_p.dvd_of_dvd_pow
    rw [← this]
    apply dvd_mul_right
  have : p ∣ Nat.gcd m n := by apply Nat.dvd_gcd <;> assumption
  have : p ∣ 1 := by
    convert this
    symm
    exact coprime_mn
  have : 2 ≤ 1 := by
    apply prime_p.two_le.trans
    exact Nat.le_of_dvd zero_lt_one this
  norm_num at this

og_raw:
example {m n p : ℕ} (nnz : n ≠ 0) (prime_p : p.Prime) : m ^ 2 ≠ p * n ^ 2  := by
  intro sqr_eq
  have nsqr_nez : n ^ 2 ≠ 0 := by simpa
  have eq1 : Nat.factorization (m ^ 2) p = 2 * m.factorization p := by
    rw [factorization_pow']
  have eq2 : (p * n ^ 2).factorization p = 2 * n.factorization p + 1 := by
    rw [factorization_mul' prime_p.ne_zero nsqr_nez, prime_p.factorization', factorization_pow',
      add_comm]
  have : 2 * m.factorization p % 2 = (2 * n.factorization p + 1) % 2 := by
    rw [← eq1, sqr_eq, eq2]
  rw [add_comm, Nat.add_mul_mod_self_left, Nat.mul_mod_right] at this
  norm_num at this

example {m n k r : ℕ} (nnz : n ≠ 0) (pow_eq : m ^ k = r * n ^ k) {p : ℕ} :
    k ∣ r.factorization p
og_raw:
example {m n k r : ℕ} (nnz : n ≠ 0) (pow_eq : m ^ k = r * n ^ k) {p : ℕ} :
    k ∣ r.factorization p  := by
  rcases r with _ | r
  · simp
  have npow_nz : n ^ k ≠ 0 := fun npowz ↦ nnz (pow_eq_zero npowz)
  have eq1 : (m ^ k).factorization p = k * m.factorization p := by
    rw [factorization_pow']
  have eq2 : ((r + 1) * n ^ k).factorization p =
      k * n.factorization p + (r + 1).factorization p := by
    rw [factorization_mul' r.succ_ne_zero npow_nz, factorization_pow', add_comm]
  have : r.succ.factorization p = k * m.factorization p - k * n.factorization p := by
    rw [← eq1, pow_eq, eq2, add_comm, Nat.add_sub_cancel]
  rw [this]
  apply Nat.dvd_sub' <;>
  apply Nat.dvd_mul_right
new_raw:
example {m n k r : ℕ} (nnz : n ≠ 0) (pow_eq : m ^ k = r * n ^ k) {p : ℕ} :
    k ∣ r.factorization p  := by
  rcases r with _ | r
  · simp
  have npow_nz : n ^ k ≠ 0 := fun npowz ↦ nnz (pow_eq_zero npowz)
  have eq1 : (m ^ k).factorization p = k * m.factorization p := by
    rw [factorization_pow']
  have eq2 : ((r + 1) * n ^ k).factorization p =
      k * n.factorization p + (r + 1).factorization p := by
    rw [factorization_mul' r.succ_ne_zero npow_nz, factorization_pow', add_comm]
  have : r.succ.factorization p = k * m.factorization p - k * n.factorization p := by
    rw [← eq1, pow_eq, eq2, add_comm, Nat.add_sub_cancel]
  rw [this]
  apply Nat.dvd_sub' <;>
  apply Nat.dvd_mul_right

decl:
theorem my_lemma4 :
    ∀ {x y ε : ℝ}, 0 < ε → ε ≤ 1 → |x| < ε → |y| < ε → |x * y| < ε
og_raw:
theorem my_lemma4 :
    ∀ {x y ε : ℝ}, 0 < ε → ε ≤ 1 → |x| < ε → |y| < ε → |x * y| < ε  := by
  intro x y ε epos ele1 xlt ylt
  calc
    |x * y| = |x| * |y| := by apply abs_mul
    _ ≤ |x| * ε := by apply mul_le_mul; linarith; linarith; apply abs_nonneg; apply abs_nonneg;
    _ < 1 * ε := by rw [mul_lt_mul_right epos]; linarith
    _ = ε := by apply one_mul
new_raw:
theorem my_lemma4 :
    ∀ {x y ε : ℝ}, 0 < ε → ε ≤ 1 → |x| < ε → |y| < ε → |x * y| < ε  := by
  intro x y ε epos ele1 xlt ylt
  calc
    |x * y| = |x| * |y| := by apply abs_mul
    _ ≤ |x| * ε := by apply mul_le_mul; linarith; linarith; apply abs_nonneg; apply abs_nonneg;
    _ < 1 * ε := by rw [mul_lt_mul_right epos]; linarith
    _ = ε := by apply one_mul

decl: example {m n : ℕ} (coprime_mn : m.Coprime n) : m ^ 2 ≠ 2 * n ^ 2
og_raw:
example {m n : ℕ} (coprime_mn : m.Coprime n) : m ^ 2 ≠ 2 * n ^ 2  := by
  intro sqr_eq
  have : 2 ∣ m := by
    apply even_of_even_sqr
    rw [sqr_eq]
    apply dvd_mul_right
  obtain ⟨k, meq⟩ := dvd_iff_exists_eq_mul_left.mp this
  have : 2 * (2 * k ^ 2) = 2 * n ^ 2 := by
    rw [← sqr_eq, meq]
    ring
  have : 2 * k ^ 2 = n ^ 2 :=
    (mul_right_inj' (by norm_num)).mp this
  have : 2 ∣ n := by
    apply even_of_even_sqr
    rw [← this]
    apply dvd_mul_right
  have : 2 ∣ m.gcd n := by
    apply Nat.dvd_gcd <;>
    assumption
  have : 2 ∣ 1 := by
    convert this
    symm
    exact coprime_mn
  norm_num at this
new_raw:

    rw [sqr_eq]
    apply dvd_mul_right
  obtain ⟨k, meq⟩ := dvd_iff_exists_eq_mul_left.mp this
  have : 2 * (2 * k ^ 2) = 2 * n ^ 2 := by
    rw [← sqr_eq, meq]
    ring
  have : 2 * k ^ 2 = n ^ 2 :=
    (mul_right_inj' (by norm_num)).mp this
  have : 2 ∣ n := by
    apply even_of_even_sqr
    rw [← this]
    apply dvd_mul_right
  have : 2 ∣ m.gcd n := by

    assumption
  have : 2 ∣ 1 := by
    convert this
    symm
    exact coprime_mn
  norm_num at this

decl: example {m n p : ℕ} (coprime_mn : m.Coprime n) (prime_p : p.Prime) : m ^ 2 ≠ p * n ^ 2
og_raw:
example {m n p : ℕ} (coprime_mn : m.Coprime n) (prime_p : p.Prime) : m ^ 2 ≠ p * n ^ 2  := by
  intro sqr_eq
  have : p ∣ m := by
    apply prime_p.dvd_of_dvd_pow
    rw [sqr_eq]
    apply dvd_mul_right
  obtain ⟨k, meq⟩ := dvd_iff_exists_eq_mul_left.mp this
  have : p * (p * k ^ 2) = p * n ^ 2 := by
    rw [← sqr_eq, meq]
    ring
  have : p * k ^ 2 = n ^ 2 := by
    apply (mul_right_inj' _).mp this
    exact prime_p.ne_zero
  have : p ∣ n := by
    apply prime_p.dvd_of_dvd_pow
    rw [← this]
    apply dvd_mul_right
  have : p ∣ Nat.gcd m n := by apply Nat.dvd_gcd <;> assumption
  have : p ∣ 1 := by
    convert this
    symm
    exact coprime_mn
  have : 2 ≤ 1 := by
    apply prime_p.two_le.trans
    exact Nat.le_of_dvd zero_lt_one this
  norm_num at this
new_raw:
example {m n p : ℕ} (coprime_mn : m.Coprime n) (prime_p : p.Prime) : m ^ 2 ≠ p * n ^ 2   := by
  intro sqr_eq
  have : p ∣ m := prime_p.dvd_of_dvd_pow (by rw [sqr_eq]; apply dvd_mul_right)
  obtain ⟨k, meq⟩ := dvd_iff_exists_eq_mul_left.mp this
  have : p * k ^ 2 = n ^ 2 := (mul_right_inj' prime_p.ne_zero).mp (by rw [← sqr_eq, meq]; ring)
  have : p ∣ n := prime_p.dvd_of_dvd_pow (by rw [← this]; apply dvd_mul_right)
  have : p ∣ Nat.gcd m n := Nat.dvd_gcd ‹p ∣ m› ‹p ∣ n›
  have : p ∣ 1 := by convert this; rw [coprime_mn]
  have : 2 ≤ 1 := prime_p.two_le.trans (Nat.le_of_dvd zero_lt_one ‹p ∣ 1›)
  norm_num at this

theorem my_lemma4 :
    ∀ {x y ε : ℝ}, 0 < ε → ε ≤ 1 → |x| < ε → |y| < ε → |x * y| < ε
og_raw:
theorem my_lemma4 :
    ∀ {x y ε : ℝ}, 0 < ε → ε ≤ 1 → |x| < ε → |y| < ε → |x * y| < ε  := by
  intro x y ε epos ele1 xlt ylt
  calc
    |x * y| = |x| * |y| := by apply abs_mul
    _ ≤ |x| * ε := by apply mul_le_mul; linarith; linarith; apply abs_nonneg; apply abs_nonneg;
    _ < 1 * ε := by rw [mul_lt_mul_right epos]; linarith
    _ = ε := by apply one_mul

  intro x y ε epos ele1 xlt ylt
  calc
    |x * y| = |x| * |y| := by apply abs_mul
    _ ≤ |x| * ε := by apply mul_le_mul; linarith; linarith; apply abs_nonneg; apply abs_nonneg;
    _ < 1 * ε := by rw [mul_lt_mul_right epos]; linarith
    _ = ε := by apply one_mul

  simp only [mem_union, mem_iInter]
  constructor

    · intro i
      right
      exact xs
    intro i
    left
    exact xI i
  intro h
  by_cases xs : x ∈ s
  · left
    exact xs
  right
  intro i
  cases h i
  · assumption
  contradiction

  constructor
  · exact fun | Or.inl xs => fun _ => Or.inr xs | Or.inr xI => fun i => Or.inl (xI i)
  · exact fun h => Or.elim (Classical.em (x ∈ s)) Or.inl (fun h' => Or.inr fun i => (h i).resolve_right h')

decl: example {m n : ℕ} (coprime_mn : m.Coprime n) : m ^ 2 ≠ 2 * n ^ 2
og_raw:
example {m n : ℕ} (coprime_mn : m.Coprime n) : m ^ 2 ≠ 2 * n ^ 2  := by
  intro sqr_eq
  have : 2 ∣ m := by
    apply even_of_even_sqr
    rw [sqr_eq]
    apply dvd_mul_right
  obtain ⟨k, meq⟩ := dvd_iff_exists_eq_mul_left.mp this
  have : 2 * (2 * k ^ 2) = 2 * n ^ 2 := by
    rw [← sqr_eq, meq]
    ring
  have : 2 * k ^ 2 = n ^ 2 :=
    (mul_right_inj' (by norm_num)).mp this
  have : 2 ∣ n := by
    apply even_of_even_sqr
    rw [← this]
    apply dvd_mul_right
  have : 2 ∣ m.gcd n := by
    apply Nat.dvd_gcd <;>
    assumption
  have : 2 ∣ 1 := by
    convert this
    symm
    exact coprime_mn
  norm_num at this
new_raw:
example {m n : ℕ} (coprime_mn : m.Coprime n) : m ^ 2 ≠ 2 * n ^ 2   := by
  intro sqr_eq
  have : 2 ∣ m := even_of_even_sqr (by rw [sqr_eq]; apply dvd_mul_right)
  obtain ⟨k, meq⟩ := dvd_iff_exists_eq_mul_left.mp this
  have : 2 * (2 * k ^ 2) = 2 * n ^ 2 := by rw [← sqr_eq, meq]; ring
  have : 2 * k ^ 2 = n ^ 2 := (mul_right_inj' (by norm_num)).mp this
  have : 2 ∣ n := even_of_even_sqr (by rw [← this]; apply dvd_mul_right)
  have : 2 ∣ m.gcd n := Nat.dvd_gcd ‹2 ∣ m› ‹2 ∣ n›
  have : 2 ∣ 1 := by convert this; symm; exact coprime_mn
  norm_num at this

decl: example {m n p : ℕ} (coprime_mn : m.Coprime n) (prime_p : p.Prime) : m ^ 2 ≠ p * n ^ 2
og_raw:
example {m n p : ℕ} (coprime_mn : m.Coprime n) (prime_p : p.Prime) : m ^ 2 ≠ p * n ^ 2  := by
  intro sqr_eq
  have : p ∣ m := by
    apply prime_p.dvd_of_dvd_pow
    rw [sqr_eq]
    apply dvd_mul_right
  obtain ⟨k, meq⟩ := dvd_iff_exists_eq_mul_left.mp this
  have : p * (p * k ^ 2) = p * n ^ 2 := by
    rw [← sqr_eq, meq]
    ring
  have : p * k ^ 2 = n ^ 2 := by
    apply (mul_right_inj' _).mp this
    exact prime_p.ne_zero
  have : p ∣ n := by
    apply prime_p.dvd_of_dvd_pow
    rw [← this]
    apply dvd_mul_right
  have : p ∣ Nat.gcd m n := by apply Nat.dvd_gcd <;> assumption
  have : p ∣ 1 := by
    convert this
    symm
    exact coprime_mn
  have : 2 ≤ 1 := by
    apply prime_p.two_le.trans
    exact Nat.le_of_dvd zero_lt_one this
  norm_num at this
new_raw:
example {m n p : ℕ} (coprime_mn : m.Coprime n) (prime_p : p.Prime) : m ^ 2 ≠ p * n ^ 2   := by
  intro sqr_eq
  have : p ∣ m := prime_p.dvd_of_dvd_pow (sqr_eq ▸ dvd_mul_right p (n ^ 2))
  obtain ⟨k, rfl⟩ := dvd_iff_exists_eq_mul_left.mp this
  have : p * k ^ 2 = n ^ 2 := (mul_right_inj' prime_p.ne_zero).mp (by rw [←sqr_eq]; ring)
  have : p ∣ n := prime_p.dvd_of_dvd_pow (this ▸ dvd_mul_right p (k ^ 2))
  have : p ∣ Nat.gcd (k * p) n := Nat.dvd_gcd ‹p ∣ k * p› ‹p ∣ n›
  have : p ∣ 1 := by rwa [coprime_mn] at this
  exact prime_p.not_dvd_one this

decl: example {m n p : ℕ} (nnz : n ≠ 0) (prime_p : p.Prime) : m ^ 2 ≠ p * n ^ 2
og_raw:
example {m n p : ℕ} (nnz : n ≠ 0) (prime_p : p.Prime) : m ^ 2 ≠ p * n ^ 2  := by
  intro sqr_eq
  have nsqr_nez : n ^ 2 ≠ 0 := by simpa
  have eq1 : Nat.factorization (m ^ 2) p = 2 * m.factorization p := by
    rw [factorization_pow']
  have eq2 : (p * n ^ 2).factorization p = 2 * n.factorization p + 1 := by
    rw [factorization_mul' prime_p.ne_zero nsqr_nez, prime_p.factorization', factorization_pow',
      add_comm]
  have : 2 * m.factorization p % 2 = (2 * n.factorization p + 1) % 2 := by
    rw [← eq1, sqr_eq, eq2]
  rw [add_comm, Nat.add_mul_mod_self_left, Nat.mul_mod_right] at this
  norm_num at this

og_raw:
example {m n k r : ℕ} (nnz : n ≠ 0) (pow_eq : m ^ k = r * n ^ k) {p : ℕ} :
    k ∣ r.factorization p  := by
  rcases r with _ | r
  · simp
  have npow_nz : n ^ k ≠ 0 := fun npowz ↦ nnz (pow_eq_zero npowz)
  have eq1 : (m ^ k).factorization p = k * m.factorization p := by
    rw [factorization_pow']
  have eq2 : ((r + 1) * n ^ k).factorization p =
      k * n.factorization p + (r + 1).factorization p := by
    rw [factorization_mul' r.succ_ne_zero npow_nz, factorization_pow', add_comm]
  have : r.succ.factorization p = k * m.factorization p - k * n.factorization p := by
    rw [← eq1, pow_eq, eq2, add_comm, Nat.add_sub_cancel]
  rw [this]
  apply Nat.dvd_sub' <;>
  apply Nat.dvd_mul_right

theorem my_lemma4 :
    ∀ {x y ε : ℝ}, 0 < ε → ε ≤ 1 → |x| < ε → |y| < ε → |x * y| < ε
og_raw:
theorem my_lemma4 :
    ∀ {x y ε : ℝ}, 0 < ε → ε ≤ 1 → |x| < ε → |y| < ε → |x * y| < ε  := by
  intro x y ε epos ele1 xlt ylt
  calc
    |x * y| = |x| * |y| := by apply abs_mul
    _ ≤ |x| * ε := by apply mul_le_mul; linarith; linarith; apply abs_nonneg; apply abs_nonneg;
    _ < 1 * ε := by rw [mul_lt_mul_right epos]; linarith
    _ = ε := by apply one_mul

decl: example {m n : ℕ} (coprime_mn : m.Coprime n) : m ^ 2 ≠ 2 * n ^ 2
og_raw:
example {m n : ℕ} (coprime_mn : m.Coprime n) : m ^ 2 ≠ 2 * n ^ 2  := by
  intro sqr_eq
  have : 2 ∣ m := by
    apply even_of_even_sqr
    rw [sqr_eq]
    apply dvd_mul_right
  obtain ⟨k, meq⟩ := dvd_iff_exists_eq_mul_left.mp this
  have : 2 * (2 * k ^ 2) = 2 * n ^ 2 := by
    rw [← sqr_eq, meq]
    ring
  have : 2 * k ^ 2 = n ^ 2 :=
    (mul_right_inj' (by norm_num)).mp this
  have : 2 ∣ n := by
    apply even_of_even_sqr
    rw [← this]
    apply dvd_mul_right
  have : 2 ∣ m.gcd n := by
    apply Nat.dvd_gcd <;>
    assumption
  have : 2 ∣ 1 := by
    convert this
    symm
    exact coprime_mn
  norm_num at this

  obtain ⟨k, meq⟩ := dvd_iff_exists_eq_mul_left.mp this
  have : 2 * (2 * k ^ 2) = 2 * n ^ 2 := by rw [←sqr_eq, meq]; ring
  have : 2 * k ^ 2 = n ^ 2 := (mul_right_inj' (by norm_num)).mp this
  have : 2 ∣ n := by apply even_of_even_sqr; rw [←this]; apply dvd_mul_right
  have : 2 ∣ m.gcd n := by apply Nat.dvd_gcd; assumption; assumption
  have : 2 ∣ 1 := by convert this; symm; exact coprime_mn
  norm_num at this

decl: example {m n p : ℕ} (coprime_mn : m.Coprime n) (prime_p : p.Prime) : m ^ 2 ≠ p * n ^ 2
og_raw:

  intro sqr_eq
  have : p ∣ m := by
    apply prime_p.dvd_of_dvd_pow
    rw [sqr_eq]
    apply dvd_mul_right
  obtain ⟨k, meq⟩ := dvd_iff_exists_eq_mul_left.mp this
  have : p * (p * k ^ 2) = p * n ^ 2 := by
    rw [← sqr_eq, meq]
    ring
  have : p * k ^ 2 = n ^ 2 := by
    apply (mul_right_inj' _).mp this
    exact prime_p.ne_zero
  have : p ∣ n := by
    apply prime_p.dvd_of_dvd_pow
    rw [← this]
    apply dvd_mul_right
  have : p ∣ Nat.gcd m n := by apply Nat.dvd_gcd <;> assumption
  have : p ∣ 1 := by
    convert this
    symm
    exact coprime_mn
  have : 2 ≤ 1 := by
    apply prime_p.two_le.trans
    exact Nat.le_of_dvd zero_lt_one this
  norm_num at this
